## F1 — MEDIUM — `SignalEfficiencyRatio` is cross-session contaminated at the first eligible signal bar

`research_indicators.py:168` calls `efficiency_ratio(rth["Close"], window=20)`
WITHOUT session grouping. `efficiency_ratio` (trend.py:102) uses `series.diff()`
and `series.diff(window)` on the RTH-filtered, multi-session series. At the first
bar that can produce a signal (`SignalBarsSinceOpen == 19`, i.e. rth bar 20 ==
`SIGNAL_MIN_BARS`), `diff(20)` and the 20-bar `abs_moves.rolling` window both
reach back one position into the PRIOR session's last RTH bar, injecting the
overnight gap into both numerator (net move) and denominator (path length).

This is the exact Method-2 substrate family already fixed for SignalRealizedVol /
SignalAutoCorr / SignalVarRatio / SignalKyleLambda — but efficiency_ratio was
missed. Note the asymmetry:
- `realized_volatility` (volatility.py:93) carries an explicit "Does not reset...
  caller is responsible" comment AND its caller wraps it in
  `groupby(session).transform(...)`.
- `efficiency_ratio` has NO such comment and its caller does NOT group it.

Measured impact on the live discovery artifact (`context_trades.csv`, 3585 rows):
- 249 trades (6.9%) enter at `SignalBarsSinceOpen == 19`.
- Their SignalEfficiencyRatio: mean 0.401 vs 0.295 for later bars — a clear
  upward bias (~+36% relative).
- Cross-check: SignalRealizedVol is NaN for EXACTLY those same 249 trades
  (correct — there is no full 20-bar in-session window yet). efficiency_ratio
  should likewise be NaN there but instead emits a contaminated value.

Why tests didn't catch it: `test_batch4_efficiency_ratio_is_nan_before_window_
and_one_for_trend` uses a SINGLE session, so at relative position 19 `diff(20)`
reads out-of-bounds → NaN and the test passes. Multi-session data reads the prior
session instead. A single-session test is structurally incapable of catching a
cross-session leak.

Fix (both parts required):
1. Session-group efficiency_ratio in research_indicators.py, mirroring
   `_session_realized_volatility` (groupby(session).transform). After the fix the
   249 boundary trades become NaN, matching SignalRealizedVol.
2. Add a session-boundary reset test for SignalEfficiencyRatio mirroring
   `test_price_change_research_context_resets_at_session_boundary` (assert the
   second session's first 20 bars are NaN). Single-session tests are not
   sufficient for any indicator that uses `.diff()` / `.shift()` / `.rolling()`.

