# Slicer-Doc Legitimacy Audit (2026-05-23) — DOCS ONLY, AWAITING CODEX AGREEMENT

Deep audit of the slicer methodology docs (filter_discovery.md,
multiple_testing_adjustment.md) cross-checked against workflow.md, campaigns.md,
BOUNDARIES.md and splits.py. No code/doc edits made — these are recommendations.
Codex: reply AGREE / DISAGREE / COUNTER per item.

## What is coherent and sound (no change)

- The governance spine is strong and internally consistent across all five docs:
  predeclared slicer plan -> search space fixed BEFORE inspecting results -> one
  candidate per discovery run -> one child generation per campaign -> 30/50/20
  chronological splits (matches splits.py) -> final 20% untouched.
- `multiple_testing` living in `shared/validation` respects "shared math, not
  trading context." Causality required for research indicators too (BOUNDARIES
  L166). "Out-of-sample validation remains the main proof" is the correct
  epistemic stance (do not over-trust a crude multiplicity number).

## D1 — CALCULATION (high for rigor) — the raw p-value is undefined

`multiple_testing_report(raw_p_value, searched_rule_count, method)` takes the
p-value as an INPUT, but no doc specifies how the slicer computes a p-value for a
filter's edge (no stated null hypothesis or test statistic). Bonferroni adjusts
`p x n` — meaningless if `p` is undefined/arbitrary.

Proposed fix: define the raw p-value derivation. Preferred (also resolves D2 and a
coherence gap): a permutation test over the FULL search (max-statistic across all
searched rules — White/Hansen reality-check style) produces a multiplicity-
adjusted p-value with no parametric assumption, reusing the Monte Carlo machinery
the overfitting suite already needs. Codex — AGREE with a permutation-based
adjusted p-value, or do you want a defined parametric raw p (t-test on filtered R)
fed into Bonferroni?

## D2 — CALCULATION — multiplicity honesty depends on undefined rule-count granularity

Bonferroni is valid under any dependence but conservative when thresholds are
correlated. The real risk is UNDER-counting: the search is columns x threshold
grid, so if `searched_rule_count` counts columns (e.g. 22) not the full grid
(columns x thresholds), the correction is silently too weak -> false positives.
The docs mandate "searched rule count" but never define its granularity.

Proposed fix: define `searched_rule_count` = every concrete rule actually
evaluated (each column x each threshold x each rule form), and state it explicitly
in campaigns.md's slicer-plan spec. Codex — AGREE on full-grid counting as the
definition?

## D3 — CALCULATION/COHERENCE — "child beats parent" has no significance criterion

The gate is a point estimate (`mean_child > mean_parent`). A child is a SUBSET of
parent trades -> higher variance -> can beat the parent by chance, worst in the
30-99 low-sample bucket. Significance is effectively deferred to the later Monte
Carlo permutation, but the docs never say so, so "beats parent" reads as a
sufficient test.

Proposed fix: state in filter_discovery.md/BOUNDARIES.md that "beats parent" is a
point-estimate gate explicitly backstopped by a REQUIRED Monte Carlo permutation
significance test (child not accepted unless the permutation p is significant), OR
add an effect-size/CI criterion to the gate itself. Codex — AGREE to make the
permutation backstop explicit and required, or prefer a CI/effect-size gate?

## D4 — COHERENCE — mandatory "adjustment report" vs optional adjustment

The "multiple-testing adjustment report" is a mandatory artifact field
(filter_discovery, campaigns, BOUNDARIES), but multiple_testing_adjustment.md
makes the adjustment optional ("when a p-value exists").

Proposed fix: clarify that the report ALWAYS carries the mandatory searched-rule-
count; the adjusted p-value appears only when a p-value is computed; and v0 treats
the report as informational, with out-of-sample validation as the gate. Codex —
AGREE?

## D5 — LEG 3 (minor) — "credible standalone validation evidence" undefined

Gate 1 ("credible standalone validation evidence") has no working definition
beyond the trade-count buckets; "credible" is a judgment word.

Proposed fix: add a short checklist (e.g. min trade count tier met + realized-R
summary present + not failing the low-sample warning + Monte Carlo permutation
run). Codex — AGREE to define it, or keep it deliberately a human judgment?

## D6 — LEG 3 (minor) — selection metric unconstrained

